---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import FocusGame from '../components/FocusGame.astro';
---

<Layout>
	<main>
		<FocusGame />

		<!-- ============================================================
		     SEO content — keyword-targeted copy about the tool. Sits
		     below the game so it never competes with the interactive
		     surface, but is fully crawlable, server-rendered HTML.
		     ============================================================ -->
		<article class="bg-canvas-parchment text-ink">
			<div class="mx-auto max-w-180 px-6 py-(--spacing-section)">
			<h2 class="text-hero text-ink">How to Increase Focus and Attention Span</h2>
			<p class="text-lead text-ink-muted-80 mt-5">
				focus-attention is a free brain game built to answer one of the most common
				questions people ask today: <strong>how to increase focus</strong> in a world
				engineered for distraction. Instead of another article full of tips, it gives you
				a measurable way to train and track your concentration — one short session at a time.
			</p>

			<h3 class="text-display-lg text-ink mt-12">The best game to increase focus</h3>
			<p class="text-ink-muted-80 mt-4">
				The rules are simple, which is exactly why it works. A new everyday word appears at
				a pace you choose. Your only job is to hold the sequence in your mind, in order, until
				the timer ends. Then you recall it. That single loop — watch, hold, recall — is a
				focused-attention exercise, and it turns out to be the
				<strong>best game to increase focus</strong> precisely because it removes everything
				else. There is no scoring gimmick, no flashing reward, nothing to grab your attention
				away from the task. Just you and the words. Most people are surprised how quickly their
				mind wants to wander, and how much steadier it gets with practice.
			</p>

			<h3 class="text-display-lg text-ink mt-12">How to increase focus and attention span</h3>
			<p class="text-ink-muted-80 mt-4">
				Attention is trainable. Like a muscle, your <strong>attention span</strong> responds to
				deliberate, repeated effort — and it shrinks when it is never challenged. focus-attention
				lets you start with a ten-second hold and gradually stretch to minutes or even hours as
				you improve. By increasing the duration a little at a time, you are practising exactly
				<strong>how to increase focus and attention span</strong> in a way that is concrete and
				honest: the timer doesn't lie. The game reports your real attention span as the length of
				time you actually held your concentration, so progress is something you can see rather than
				guess at.
			</p>

			<h3 class="text-display-lg text-ink mt-12">How to increase focus and memory together</h3>
			<p class="text-ink-muted-80 mt-4">
				Focus and memory are two sides of the same coin — you cannot remember what you never
				properly attended to. Because the game asks you to recall the sequence in the correct
				order, it trains working memory and concentration in the same breath. If you have been
				looking for <strong>how to increase focus and memory</strong> without dry flashcards or
				subscriptions, this is a genuinely enjoyable alternative. Each round is a small,
				self-contained test of <strong>how to improve memory</strong> under mild time pressure,
				which is the kind of practice that transfers to everyday tasks like reading, studying,
				and holding a conversation without losing the thread.
			</p>

			<h3 class="text-display-lg text-ink mt-12">A brain game with no fluff</h3>
			<p class="text-ink-muted-80 mt-4">
				Plenty of apps promise a smarter you. focus-attention is a deliberately minimal
				<strong>brain game</strong>: it runs free in your browser, needs no download, and respects
				your time. Choose how long you want to focus and how often a new word appears, then begin.
				When the timer ends, rebuild the sequence from a clean, alphabetically sorted list so the
				challenge stays on memory and order — not on hunting for a word. You get two clear metrics:
				your attention span (how long you held focus) and your focus score (the percentage of the
				sequence you rebuilt correctly).
			</p>

			<h3 class="text-display-lg text-ink mt-12">Build the habit</h3>
			<p class="text-ink-muted-80 mt-4">
				The honest answer to <strong>how to increase focus</strong> is consistency. A few
				deliberate minutes a day beats an occasional marathon. Play a quick round between tasks,
				push your duration a little further each week, and watch your numbers climb on the
				leaderboard. Whether you are a student preparing for exams, a professional fighting a noisy
				inbox, or simply someone who wants a sharper mind, this is a small daily ritual that pays
				off. Start your first round above — it takes ten seconds to find out where your
				<strong>attention span</strong> stands today.
			</p>
			</div>
		</article>
	</main>

	<footer class="bg-canvas-parchment text-ink-muted-80 px-6 py-12 text-center">
		<p class="text-caption">focus-attention.com — train your attention span, one sequence at a time.</p>
		<p class="text-fine text-ink-muted-48 mt-2">
			A word appears at the pace you choose. Hold the order. Recall it when the timer ends.
		</p>
	</footer>
</Layout>
